            <div id="warnings" class="hideme" style="padding:0px;">
              <div class="probHeader"><h2 style="margin:0px">Dashboard Warning Lights</h2>
              <p>What they mean and how to fix them.</p></div>
              <!-- PUT WARNING LIGHTS DATA HERE -->
              <div class="text-center">
                <span class="dropt">
                <%=image_tag('warnings/001.png', :id => "001png", class: 'warning', title: "Oil Pressure Warning - this light will illuminate when the oil pressure sensor detects low oil pressure, the vehicle's engine should be switched of immediately to avoid severe engine damage and the oil level checked to ensure correct quantity in the engine.", :onclick=>"populateData('input040','Oil Pressure Light','input040close');".html_safe)%>
                </span>
                <span class="dropt">
                <%=image_tag('warnings/002.png', :id => "002png", class: 'warning', title: "Battery Warning - This means the vehicle has stopped charging the battery and will eventually go flat. Seek professional help to resolve the issue.", :onclick=>"populateData('input041','Battery Warning Light','input041close');".html_safe)%>
                </span>
                <span class="dropt">
                <%=image_tag('warnings/004.png', :id => "004png", class: 'warning', title: "Front Airbag - Indicates a fault with the airbag system and disables the airbag function, this is now an MOT failure when presented with the light illuminated. Amber light informs the driver when a passenger air bag has been switched of manually.", :onclick=>"populateData('input042','Front Airbag Light','input042close');".html_safe)%>
                </span>
                <span class="dropt">
                <%=image_tag('warnings/005.png', :id => "005png", class: 'warning', title: "Temperature Warning Light - it warns the driver when the engine is overheating and usually demands the driver to stop the vehicle and seek attention to rectify the fault.", :onclick=>"populateData('input043','Temperature Warning Light','input043close');".html_safe)%>
                </span>
                <span class="dropt">
                <%=image_tag('warnings/010.png', id: "010png", class: 'warning', title: "ABS Warning Light - ABS Warning Light - this light will show when you have a fault in the ABS braking system, this will not result in losing your brakes but additional safety features will have been switched of by the control module, professional help should be sought to resolve the issues. Note: The light illuminates briefly on engine start up but switches of automatically.", onclick: "populateData('input044','ABS Warning Light','input044close');".html_safe)%>
                </span>
                <span class="dropt">
                <%=image_tag('warnings/011.png', :id => "011png", class: 'warning', title: "Engine Management Light - this light illuminates when the vehicle detects a fault with the engine management system usually related to emissions or running concerns. Can cause the vehicle to go into limp home mode when illuminated with a loss of engine power, this light require's immediate professional attention to prevent damage to expensive exhaust components.", :onclick=>"populateData('input045','Engine Light','input045close');".html_safe)%>
                </span>
                <span class="dropt">
                <%=image_tag('warnings/016.png', :id => "016png", class: 'warning', title: "Warning Light - this light will illuminate with other lights and is usually accompanied by an error message in the display", :onclick=>"populateData('input046','Warning Light','input046close');".html_safe)%>
